        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 7:44PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 743 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from Birch Run to near Flint to near Brighton. Movement was
east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Goodland Township, Waterford, Ortonville, Rankin, Holly State
Recreation Area, North Branch, Mayville, Silverwood, Auburn Hills,
Genesee, Lake Angelus, Vassar, Crossroads Village, Leonard, Atlas,
Almont, Mount Morris, East Dayton, Hartland, and Otter Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
